(3)Feed My People Food Bank, 2610 Alpine Road, Eau Claire, WI 54703, USA.

A focus group process, conducted by a community-academic partnership, 
qualitatively assessed food insecurity perspectives of parents and community 
staff assisting families with food assistance. Food insecurity was reported to 
affect all aspects of their life, increasing stress and reducing coping 
abilities. The Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality encourages research 
with priority populations, including low-income populations. This research 
supports the body of knowledge correlating relationships between poverty, food 
insecurity, and chronic health conditions. Perspectives of food-insecure people 
are often missing from policy and advocacy interventions. Nurses can use lessons 
learned and recommendations from this research to address 
food-insecurity-related health disparities.

